<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09118k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09118k">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09118k"> 118(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> darkness of <font face="wake">+</font> death ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Under the reign of Tiberius, the whole earth, or at least a celebrated province of the Roman empire, was involved in a preternatural <mark>darkness of three hours</mark>. Even this miraculous event, which ought to have excited the wonder, the curiosity, and the devotion of mankind, passed without notice in an age of science and history. <small> Edward Gibbon, <a name="EGDF2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGDF2"><cite title="source">Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire</cite></a> (ed. unknown) II, 219 (Chapter XV)</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
